[{"id":"VR217179","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p class=\"title_line passage-title\">&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A. Describe the topography shown in Image 1.</p>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">B. Based on the physical characteristics of the landscape shown in Image 2, explain why people adopted the land use practice shown in the image.</p>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">C. Explain a negative effect that irrigation may have on water quality.</p>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">D. Explain the degree to which mechanized irrigation has increased economies of scale within the agricultural sector.</p>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">E. Explain why large-scale commercial agricultural operations are increasingly replacing small family farms in developed countries.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR217179_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p class=\"title_line passage-title\"><span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">IMAGE 1: CENTER PIVOT IRRIGATION, CIMARRON, KANSAS, UNITED STATES</span></p>\n</div>\n<img alt=\"The figure presents a picture titled “Image 1: Center Pivot Irrigation, Cimarron, Kansas, United States.” The picture shows a section of seemingly flat farmland that is divided into a grid of many square plots of equal size. A circular pattern is apparent in each square where the circle diameter is equal to the side length of the square. A key indicates a distance of slightly less than 1 inch represents 2 miles. Approximately three square plots span the space of 2 miles, and the total area of land in the picture is approximately 5 miles by 16 miles.\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR217179.g01.png\" width=\"600\" /></div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p class=\"title_line passage-title\"><span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">IMAGE 2: IRRIGATED TERRACES, YUANYANG, YUNNAN, CHINA</span></p>\n</div>\n<img alt=\"The figure presents a picture titled “Image 2: Irrigated Terraces, Yuanyang, Yunnan, China.” The picture shows a section of farmland that has variations in shading that indicates variations in elevation. There are lines throughout the picture that seem to follow the natural contours of the land. The space between lines is greater in areas of little apparent change in elevation, and the space between lines is less in areas of greater changes in elevation. A key indicates a distance of slightly less than a half inch represents 150 feet, so the total area of land in the picture is approximately 2,500 feet by 1,500 feet.\" height=\"359\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR217179.g02.png\" width=\"600\" /><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\">Source: Esri Data Partners</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Cultural practices such as land use may vary across geographical locations because of physical geography and available resources. The images illustrate two different ways humans have modified the natural landscape.</p>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">&nbsp;</p>\n"}]}]